article_title: Political Diary: Pell Runs for Rhode Island Governor
article_text:
Democrat Clay Pell has never held elected office. He's best known as the grandson of former Sen. Claiborne Pell (of Pell Grant fame), and husband of world figure-skating champion Michelle Kwan. Yet he's launching a bid for governor in his home-state of Rhode Island against two widely respected Democrats. What's he thinking?

Well, for starters, the party's primary isn't until September, so he has plenty of time to introduce himself to voters. Like other Rhode Island political dynasties (Chafee, Caprio) the Pell name also...
